at we had been there for the better part of a day.   They said they didnt care, they would KS us and get the kill.  "<i> Lodizal is a FFA mob </i>" they said.<br><br>What the fook?  Who in thier right mind that has graced the levels post 50 still believes in free for all mobs?   There's no <i>respect</i> anymore.    What are people thinking when they try and run over people to get something like this?   Its kill stealing.   I dont care if you hit the mob first, got hit by the mob first, saw the mob first (The Vision tm).   We put in the hard time for the mob,  get lost.<br><br>I would like to mention this, however.   At somewhere around the 30 hour mark,  i had to get some sleep and did so for the remainder of the night.  When i woke up,  a Twist of Fate was there for thier first Lodi.   We checked around the Lodi camp, but couldnt see them, so we sat down.   aToF gathered closeby and i soon recieved a tell from Torm. (guildleader) I told her how long id been there already, and that i had timed the spawn etc etc....<br><br>aToF had 3 groups there.  They didnt know how hard Lodi was, so forgive em for having that many people.  It sounded to me like 2 people had arrived in zone, and when people logged on they just came to help,  ToF people are like that,  really nice people.  Anyways<br><br>I told Torm how long id been there, and she soon sent me a tell back saying they were gonna go do something else.   She said she respected the time id put in, and that they couldnt take the spawn from good people.<br><br>THAT is the honor that Emarr lacks.   Its funny how the people that have respect for others like Torm's guild did for me and my partner at Lodi,  get the same respect back.<br><br>Thanks Twist of Fate.   <br><br>Moongaiden<br>KX<br><br>PS:  I was there for another 42 hours until Lodi popped. You're lucky you left ;) <p>-Asti Spumate, Baby.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HRE