sn't.  Some people will try this bullshit of all outdoor mobs aren't campable, but that's wrong.  As long as it pops in the same place every time, it's campable.  People calling this mob FFA are just trying to ease their conscience for when they want to kill him and he's already camped. <p>Carathos Ollathir<br>60th level druid<br>Retired</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulumpyhammerfell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lumpy Hammerfell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 337<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/24/02 8:11:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3085.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do people think FFA is something more than blatent K</span><hr size=1> Lodi has always been about mobilization.  Whoever mobilizes the fastest and gets the kill  wins the prize.  If you bring enough people to kill him and wait for him to pop, you should have no problem with KSing.   But one person can not kill Lodi, so why camp him with one person?<br><br>Lumpy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udraelyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Draelyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/24/02 8:29:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3085.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Sage</span><hr size=1> You forgot RF bud<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Drae <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowra